"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `ax` object. The `sbn.scatterplot` function returns a `matplotlib.axes._subplots.AxesSubplot` object, which should not be reassigned to `ax` after it has been initialized by `plt.subplots()`. This causes the subsequent calls to `ax` methods to be applied to the wrong object.\",\n  \"patch\": \"14c14\\n<fig, ax = plt.subplots()\\n---\\n>fig, ax = plt.subplots()\\n16c16\\n<ax = sbn.scatterplot(data=df, x='date', y='total', hue='location', style='type')\\n---\\n>sbn.scatterplot(data=df, x='date', y='total', hue='location', style='type', ax=ax)\"\n}"